  "prompt": "Can we know if our card has been inserted in ATM?",
  "response": "Yes, modern ATMs generally have mechanisms to detect when a card has been inserted. This is typically done through sensors within the card slot that detect the presence of the card. Once the card is inserted, the ATM will usually prompt you to enter your PIN and proceed with your transaction. If the card is not properly inserted or if there is an issue with the card reader, the ATM may display an error message or prompt you to reinsert the card.",
